    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if the sovereignty argument is that strong, how would you advise my students to handle the common counter-argument that strict enforcement is inhumane or violates human rights? i want them to be able to address those criticisms without just dismissing them—how can they frame a response that shows strict enforcement and human rights aren't necessarily mutually exclusive?",
